HB 496 Original 2026 Regular Session McCormick
Abstract: Prohibits the secretary of the Dept. of Conservation and Energy from limiting the
surface injection pressure for onsite saltwater disposal wells in Bossier, Caddo, and
Webster Parishes to less than 0.5 lbs. per foot or 0.25 lbs. per foot depending on the
depth and injection volume of the well.
Present law authorizes the secretary of the Dept. of Conservation and Energy to regulate
disposal wells, including saltwater disposal wells.
Proposed law prohibits the secretary from limiting any onsite or community saltwater
disposal wells in the parishes of Bossier, Caddo, and Webster to a surface injection pressure
less than:
(1) 0.5 lbs. per vertical foot for wells deeper than 1,200 feet that inject less than 3,000
barrels per day.
(2) 0.25 lbs. per vertical foot for wells deeper than 1,200 feet that inject 3,000 barrels or
more per day.
(2) 0.25 lbs. per vertical foot for wells up to 1,200 feet deep.
